# Design: Admin Dashboard Actions Completion

## Technical Approach
Implement a shared admin write-state model and reuse it across Products, Categories, and Catalog Jobs pages. Keep all writes in `adminOperationsService` (built on `httpClient` + CSRF/auth headers), while page components handle form state and list refresh. This follows the proposal’s “shared state model” approach and avoids one-off mutation UX.

## Architecture Decisions

| Decision | Options | Tradeoff | Choice |
|---|---|---|---|
| Write-state ownership | Per-page ad hoc state vs shared reducer/hook + UI primitives | Ad hoc is faster but duplicates behavior and copy | Shared reducer/hook + `AdminPageStates` write primitives |
| Mutation boundary | Call `fetch` directly in pages vs service wrappers | Direct fetch couples transport+UI; wrappers centralize contracts/errors | Keep pages thin; all mutations/polling exposed by `adminOperationsService` |
| Error strategy | Raw thrown errors vs normalized operator-facing mapping | Raw errors are inconsistent; mapping adds minimal abstraction | Normalize to `{message, code, correlationId, fieldErrors}` using `ApiClientError` |
| CSV progress model | Fire-and-forget enqueue vs enqueue + bounded polling | Fire-and-forget hides outcome; polling needs cadence guard | Enqueue then bounded polling (`maxAttempts`, `delayMs`) with terminal feedback |

## Data Flow
```text
Product/Category Form Submit
  -> page handler sets writeState=pending
  -> adminOperationsService.create/update
  -> httpClient (auth + XSRF + JSON parse + ApiClientError)
  -> success: set writeState=success, refetch list
  -> failure: set writeState=error(mapped)

CSV Upload Submit
  -> createAdminImportJob(text/csv)
  -> awaitAdminImportTerminalStatus(jobId)
  -> terminal COMPLETED/FAILED
  -> refresh listAdminCatalogJobs + rows + report diagnostics
  -> render status banner + correlation-aware error details
```

