## Interfaces / Contracts
```ts
type AdminWriteStatus = 'idle' | 'pending' | 'success' | 'error'

interface AdminWriteFeedback {
  status: AdminWriteStatus
  message?: string
  code?: string
  correlationId?: string
  fieldErrors?: { field: string; message: string }[]
}

interface ProductUpsertPayload {
  name: string
  slug: string
  categoryId?: string | null
}

interface CategoryUpsertPayload {
  name: string
  slug: string
}
```
`mapAdminWriteError(error: unknown): AdminWriteFeedback` will convert 4xx/5xx transport errors into operator-safe copy. 4xx prioritizes field/validation messages; 5xx uses generic incident copy and includes correlationId when present.

## Testing Strategy

| Layer | What to Test | Approach |
|---|---|---|
| Component | Write-state transitions, form submit/retry, banner rendering | RTL + Vitest, mock service methods; assert pending/success/error UI and refreshed lists |
| Service | Endpoint path/method/payload and error normalization | Existing fetch-mocked service tests, add wrapper/poll/error cases |
| Integration (frontend slice) | CSV enqueue->poll->diagnostics refresh path | Page test with sequential mocked responses (QUEUED->PROCESSING->COMPLETED/FAILED) |

## Migration / Rollout
No migration required. Frontend-only change; backend contracts already exist.

